OL,5,CSTALKING THE STALKER...                
OL,7, The Royal Society for the Protection of
OL,8, Birds says 96 incidents ofCpoisoning,  
OL,9,Cshooting, trapping and nest destruction
OL,10, claimed the lives of more than 80 of   
OL,11, the UK's rarest birds of prey in 1996. 
OL,13, SpokesmanCChris HarbardGsays: "In 1995 
OL,14, there were 108 incidents which killed  
OL,15, at least 96 birds.                     
OL,17, "These figures areConly an indication  
OL,18, of what's happening in our countryside.
OL,19, The real figures are much higher."     
