OL,5,CSTALKING THE STALKER...                
OL,7, A spokesman from theCDepartment of the 
OL,8,CEnvironmentGsays birds of prey are     
OL,9, protected under the Wildlife and       
OL,10, Countryside Act 1991.                  
OL,12, She tells Teletext: "Killing birds of  
OL,13, prey isCillegalGand those who commit   
OL,14, such offences are prosecuted.          
OL,16, "However, it is often difficult to     
OL,17,Cobtain the proofGnecessary to catch    
OL,18, killers of the birds which are rapidly 
OL,19, on the decline in this country."       
